#Bash Programming 

To Define folder name on which we are working 
#! /usr/bin/bash

1) User Input:

read "username: " username
then input taken on next line

read -p "username: " username
then input taken on same line

while taking password to hide password We take -sp
eg. read -sp "password: " password

2) Array Input:

to get array we use -a flag
read -a names
echo "${names[0]}, ${names[1]}"

after read command if we dont mention any variable name then terminal have 
default variable "REPLY".
